# Frontend Documentation - Lazarus Platform

This document provides a comprehensive "start-to-finish" overview of the **Lazarus Frontend**, a modern Fintech Crowdfunding Dashboard built with React, Vite, and Tailwind CSS.

## 1. Project Overview

The frontend is a **Single Page Application (SPA)** designed to interact with the Lazarus Backend API. It features a responsive, dark-mode-first "Glassmorphism" UI, real-time data fetching, and role-based access control (RBAC).

*   **Framework**: [React 19](https://react.dev/)
*   **Build Tool**: [Vite](https://vitejs.dev/)
*   **Styling**: [Tailwind CSS v4](https://tailwindcss.com/) + Custom CSS Variables
*   **Routing**: [React Router v7](https://reactrouter.com/)
*   **Icons**: [Lucide React](https://lucide.dev/)
*   **HTTP Client**: [Axios](https://axios-http.com/)

