## 3. Core Architecture & Configuration

### A. Entry Point ([main.jsx](file:///c:/Users/Omkar%20Raut/OneDrive/Desktop/TSEC_Hacks_26/frontend/src/main.jsx))
The application is wrapped in multiple Context Providers to ensure global access to Authentication and Theme state.
```jsx
<Router>
  <AuthProvider>    {/* Handles User Session */}
    <ThemeProvider> {/* Handles UI Theme */}
      <App />
    </ThemeProvider>
  </AuthProvider>
</Router>
```

### B. Styling System ([index.css](file:///c:/Users/Omkar%20Raut/OneDrive/Desktop/TSEC_Hacks_26/frontend/src/index.css))
We effectively use **CSS Variables** for theming, allowing instant toggling between Dark (default) and Light mdoes.
*   **Variables**: defined in `:root` (e.g., `--background`, `--primary`).
*   **Tailwind Integration**: The new Tailwind v4 `@theme` directive maps these variables to utility classes.
*   **Custom Utilities**:
    *   `.glass-panel`: Applies backdrop-blur and semi-transparent gradients.
    *   `.glass-input`: Styled form inputs matching the theme of the Dashboard.

### C. API Integration ([src/utils/api.js](file:///c:/Users/Omkar%20Raut/OneDrive/Desktop/TSEC_Hacks_26/frontend/src/utils/api.js))
Instead of using [fetch](file:///c:/Users/Omkar%20Raut/OneDrive/Desktop/TSEC_Hacks_26/frontend/src/pages/AdminDashboard.jsx#16-41) or raw `axios` calls in components, we use a centralized instance.
*   **Base URL**: Loaded from `VITE_API_BASE_URL` (e.g., `http://localhost:3000/api`).
*   **Interceptors**: Automatically attaches the JWT `Authorization` header to *every* request if a user is logged in.

